<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="102" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="102">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="102">Mentum without paired foveae; antennae apically lighter than at base (Fig. 2H); dorsal surface glabrous, without microsculpture; pronotum (Fig. 3H) narrowed at base, with posterior angle approximately square or projecting slightly laterad and produced slightly anterior to base of pronotum; foretibia with apicolateral notch; elytron with two pale maculae; i8 inserted basally into deep pit between Eo2 and Eo3; i8 (if complete) distant from elytral margin at midpoint, or (if interrupted) (Fig. 4H) deeply impressed basally and apically; mesepisternum (Fig. 7A) with one or two deep pits; elytron with 4 or 5 discal setae (if 5, 2 basal setae positioned close together); only i1 and i8 visibly impressed; Eo4 distant from Eo3; ARG short, simple.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="102" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="102">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="102">Southern Africa, South Asia, and South America.</paragraph>
